What are value types?

There are two kinds of types in the java programming language
	1. Value types
	2. Reference types

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
			Java Primitive Types
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

boolean	: a logical type with valid values of true and false
byte 	: an 8 bit integer type with a range of -128 	       to +127
short 	: a 16 bit integer type with a range of -32,768        to +32,767
int	: a 32 bit integer type with a range of -2,147,483,648 to +2,147,483,647
long 	: a 64 bit integer type with a range of roughly (+/-)9 * 10 ^ 18
float	: a 32 bit floating point type with a reduced range and precision
double 	: a 64 bit floating point type with a large range and high precision
char 	: a 16 bit integer type that can store any unicode character

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Definitions :

Primitive Types 	: are all value types in Java.
Value Type Variables 	: always store a value of that type.
Assignment Statement	: stores a value in a variable.

